import app from './app'
import './database'


app.listen(4000);
console.log('server listen on port', 4000)

import {Router} from 'express'
const router = Router()

import * as productController from '../controllers/producst.controller'

router.post('/', productController.createProduct)

router.get('/', productController.getProducts)

router.get('/:productId', productController.getProductById)

router.get('/:productId', productController.updateProductById)

router.get('/:productId', productController.deleteProductById)


export default router;

import mongoose from 'mongoose'

mongoose.connect("mongodb://localhost/api-db")


    .then(db => console.log('base de datos conectando'))
    .catch(error => console.log(error))

import {Router} from 'express'
const router = Router()

import * as estudianteController from '../controllers/estudiante.controller'

router.post('/', estudianteController.createEstudiante)

router.get('/', estudianteController.getEstudiantes)

router.get('/:estudianteId', estudianteController.getEstudianteById)

router.put('/:estudianteId', estudianteController.updateEstudianteById)

router.delete('/:estudianteId', estudianteController.deleteEstudianteById)


export default router;
